testsuite.name: Proximity Reporter Suite
testsuite.details: The test cases for proximity reporter application.

testcase.name: [ble-app-pxp-reporter-tc-001]Discover local name
testcase.summary: Phone discovers the device with the correct local name.

step.actions: Download ble_app_pxp_reporter_fw.bin
Press 'Reset' Key on Board to start BLE application.
step.expectedresults:
UART terminal receives logs as below:

[APP]Local BD_ADDR-EA:CB:3E:CF:00:D0
[APP]Proximity Reporter running

step.actions: Open GRToolbox and Scan

testcase.name: [ble-app-pxp-reporter-tc-002]Display Device Appearance
testcase.summary: GRToolbox displays the device appearance.
testcase.preconditions: GRToolbox discovered the device named 'GDX_PXP_Reporter'.

step.actions: Check the icon before device name and bd addr in device list of GRToolbox.
step.expectedresults: The icon for Proximity Reporter is shown.

testcase.name: [ble-app-pxp-reporter-tc-003]Connect with BLE App
testcase.summary: Test connecting and pairing
testcase.preconditions: The IUT is in the device list of BLE App, like nRF Connect or GRToolbox.

step.actions: Click 'Connect' button of the IUT in BLE App
step.expectedresults:
BLE App is connected with IUT.

IUT  outputs log '[APP]Proximity Reporter: connected' in UART terminal.

step.actions: Expand Link Loss Service in the Connected device view of BLE App
step.expectedresults: There is 'Alert Level' characteristic in Link Loss Service.

step.actions: Click 'Read' button of 'Alert Level' characteristic.
step.expectedresults:
Phone popups an input dialog for pin code.

IUT outputs log 'Please Input pin code: 123456' in UART terminal.

step.actions: Input pin code in Phone
step.expectedresults: Pairing successfully and The value 'No Alert' of Alert Level is shown in BLE App.

testcase.name: [ble-app-pxp-reporter-tc-004]Reconnect with BLE App
testcase.summary: Test reconnection.
testcase.preconditions:
IUT had been paired with the phone.
IUT is not conneced.
IUT is advertising.

step.actions: Click 'Connect' button of the IUT in BLE App.
Expand Link Loss Service in Connected device view in BLE App.
step.expectedresults: There is 'Alert Level' characteristic in BLE App.

step.actions: Click 'Read' button of 'Alert Level' characteristic.
step.expectedresults: The value 'No Alert' of 'Alert Level' is shown without pairing procedure.

testcase.name: [ble-app-pxp-reporter-tc-005]Immediate Alert
testcase.summary: There are three alert levels: No Alert, Mild Alert and High Alert. Repeat the steps to test the three alert levels.
testcase.preconditions:
Phone has been paired with IUT.
Phone is connected with IUT.

step.actions: Expand  'Immediate Alert' Service in Connected view of BLE App.
Click 'Write' button of 'Alert Level' characteristic,  then select the alert level to send in BLE App.
step.expectedresults: IUT outputs the alert level which is sent from BLE App.

testcase.name: [ble-app-pxp-reporter-tc-006]Link Loss Alert
testcase.summary: There are three alert levels: No Alert, Mild Alert and High Alert. Repeat the steps to test the three levels.
testcase.preconditions:
Phone has been paired with IUT.
Phone is connected with IUT.

step.actions: Set Link Loss Alert level in BLE App.
Take the phone away from IUT until phone disconnects with IUT.
step.expectedresults: IUT outputs the alert level which was set in Step 1, and IUT starts the advertising.

testcase.name: [ble-app-pxp-reporter-tc-007]Tx Power Level
testcase.summary: BLE App gets the correct value of Tx Power Level.
testcase.preconditions:
Phone has been paired with IUT.
Phone is connected with IUT.

step.actions: Click 'Read' button to get the value of Tx Power Level in BLE App.
step.expectedresults: The value of Tx Power Level is shown.

step.actions: Compare the value in BLE App with the the value that is gotten from TX pwoer testing equipment.

testcase.name: Connect And Disconnect Stress Test
testcase.summary: test connect and disconnect stability of balboa platform
testcase.preconditions: install auto test app in Android phone

step.actions: download test bin in balboa platform, such as ble_app_hrs_fw.bin

open auto test app at mobile phone, set test params as:

  1.test time: 10

  2.test count: 2000

  3.scan time: 30

  4.test case: goodix_xxx

  5.test device: choice balboa name and address

  6.press down start test button
step.expectedresults: auto test app switch to test page successfully

step.actions: waiting app test finish, record test result and compare with pass standard
step.expectedresults:
app test finish successfullly

pass standard:

1. the number of successful tests must be greater than 1900

testsuite.name: System Functionality and Performance Test Suie
testsuite.details: Test cases for Deep Sleep Mode, Power Consumption, Encryption, Device Firmware Update and boot.

testcase.name: con_adv_bv_01
testcase.summary: Tests device discovery in ADV39 channel, Test conneciton establishment and disconnection.
testcase.preconditions:
Two devices that support BLE4.0 Controller features.

Abbreviation description:
DUT: The device used for testing.
RTD: The remote tester device used to test the DUT.

step.actions: DUT starts advertising in ADV39 Channel, then RTD tester scans DUT device in ADV39 Channel.
RTD tries to establish connection with DUT
RTD disconnects connection with DUT

testcase.name: con_adv_bv_02
testcase.summary: Tests device discovery, connection establishment failed when trying to initiate a connection
testcase.preconditions:
Two devices that support BLE4.2 Controller features.

Abbreviation description:
DUT: The device used for testing.
RTD: The remote tester device used to test the DUT.

step.actions: DUT starts advertising, RTD scans the DUT device.
RTD stops scanning, then RTD starts initiating connection with DUT, but DUT reset itself by HCI_RESET_CMD.
step.expectedresults: RTD establish connection failed with error code 0x3E(Connection Establishment Failed).

testcase.name: con_adv_bv_04
testcase.summary: Tests that an advertiser DUT upon receiving a connection request to the directed advertising indications, stops advertising after the reception and starts to maintain a connection in the slave role.
testcase.preconditions:
Two devices that support BLE4.2 Controller features.

Abbreviation description:
DUT: The device used for testing.
RTD: The remote tester device used to test the DUT.

step.actions: DUT starts a high duty directed advertising, RTD detect the timeout of DUT's advertising.
DUT starts another high duty directed advertising, RTD starts initiate a connection with DUT

testcase.name: con_adv_bv_06
testcase.summary: Tests that an advertiser IUT, using undirected connectable advertising with legacy PDUs, receives a connection indication on the primary channel, stops advertising after the reception, and starts to maintain a connection in the slave role.
testcase.preconditions:
Two devices that support BLE5.0 features.

Abbreviation description:
DUT: The device used for testing.
RTD: The remote tester device used to test the DUT.

step.actions: DUT starts an undirected connectable advertising with legacy PDUs, RTD starts scanning to discover DUT.
RTD establish connection with DUT.
RTD sends some acl data with data length = 14 octets to DUT for 100 times.
step.expectedresults: The acl data received successfully by DUT.

step.actions: RTD disconnects connection with DUT.

testcase.name: con_adv_bv_09
testcase.summary: Tests that an advertiser DUT receives a connection request, stops advertising after the reception and starts to maintain a connection in the slave role when the connection request indicates support for Channel Selection Algorithm #2.
testcase.preconditions:
Two devices that support BLE5.0 Controller features.

Abbreviation description:
DUT: The device used for testing.
RTD: The remote tester device used to test the DUT.

step.actions: DUT starts an advertising, RTD starts to initiate a connection with DUT.

testcase.name: con_adv_bv_10
testcase.summary: Tests that an advertiser DUT receives a connection request to the directing advertising indication, stops advertising after the reception and starts to maintain a connection in the slave role when the connection request indicates support for Channel Selection Algorithm #2.
testcase.preconditions:
Two devices that support BLE5.0 Controller features.

Abbreviation description:
DUT: The device used for testing.
RTD: The remote tester device used to test the DUT.

step.actions: DUT starts an directed advertising, RTD starts to initiate a connection with DUT.

testcase.name: con_adv_bv_11
testcase.summary: Tests that an advertiser DUT that only supports Channel Selection Algorithm #1 receives a connection request from a Lower Tester that supports Channel Section Algorithm #2.
testcase.preconditions:
1) Two devices that support BLE5.0 Controller features.

2) The DUT device shall be configured to use Channel Selection Algorithm #1.

3) Abbreviation description:
DUT: The device used for testing.
RTD: The remote tester device used to test the DUT.

step.actions: Configure DUT only support Channel Selection Algorithm #1 , then DUT starts an advertising, RTD starts to initiate a connection with DUT.
step.expectedresults: Connection established successfully with HCI_LE_Channel_Selection_Algorithm_Event(Channel Selection Algorithm #1) reported.

testcase.name: con_ini_bv_01
testcase.summary: Tests that an initiator DUT sends a connection request to an advertiser and starts to maintain a connection in the master role. Test that the DUT responds with Command Disallowed to an LE Set Random Address command when initiating.
testcase.preconditions:
Two devices that support BLE5.0 Controller features.

Abbreviation description:
DUT: The device used for testing.
RTD: The remote tester device used to test the DUT.

step.actions: RTD starts an advertising, DUT starts to initiate connection with RTD, then DUT issues  an LE Set Random Address command when initiating.
step.expectedresults: Connection established successfully, DUT responds with Command Disallowed to an LE Set Random Address command when initiating.

testcase.name: con_ini_bv_02
testcase.summary: Tests that an initiator DUT sends a connection request to an advertiser using directed advertising events and starts to maintain a connection in the master role.
testcase.preconditions:
Two devices that support BLE5.0 Controller features.

Abbreviation description:
DUT: The device used for testing.
RTD: The remote tester device used to test the DUT.

step.actions: RTD starts an advertising, DUT starts to initiate connection with RTD.
DUT sends 14 octets acl data to RTD for 1000 times.
step.expectedresults: The acl data received successfully by DUT.

step.actions: RTD disconnects connection with DUT.

testcase.name: con_ini_bv_06
testcase.summary: Tests that an initiator DUT sends connection requests correctly filtering advertiser devices.
testcase.preconditions:
Two devices that support BLE5.0 features.

Abbreviation description:
DUT: The device used for testing.
RTD: The remote tester device used to test the DUT.

step.actions: DUT set white list with a public address and a random address.
RTD sends an advertising with the public address(set in DUT's white list) in AdvA, the DUT starts to initiate connection with RTD.
RTD sends an advertising with the random address(set in DUT's white list) in AdvA, the DUT starts to initiate connection with RTD.
RTD sends an advertising with the random address(not set in DUT's white list) in AdvA, the DUT starts to initiate connection with RTD.
